longBusinessSummary: Hawesko Holding AG, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the trading and sale of wines, champagnes, and other alcoholic drinks in Germany and rest of Europe. The company operates through three segments: Retail, B2B, and E-commerce. It operates a network of retail outlets under the Jacques' Wein-Depot and Wein & Co. brands. The company sells its products to end customers, various sales channels, catering trade, and retailers through specialty retail stores and wholesale operations/distribution, as well as through distance selling primarily under the Hawesko and Vinos names. As of December 31, 2020, it operated 327 Jacques' Wein-Depot outlets, as well as 21 branches of Wein & Co. in Austria. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Hamburg, Germany. Hawesko Holding AG is a subsidiary of Tocos Beteiligung GmbH.
